#1

Code 
surveys <- surveys |>
  mutate(species = as.factor(species),
         species = fct_reorder(species, 
                               weight, 
                               .desc = TRUE))

ggplot(data = surveys, 
       mapping = aes (x = weight, 
                      y = species)) + 
  geom_jitter(color = 'tomato', 
              alpha = 0.2) + 
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA)  +
  labs(x = 'Weight(g)',
       y = '',
       title = 'Plot')

#2

Code

       mapping = aes(x = year,
                     y = weight,
                     col = genus)) +

Code 
mean_weight <- surveys |>
  group_by(year, 
           genus) |>
  summarise(behave = mean(weight))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the
`.groups` argument.
Code 
ggplot(data = mean_weight,
       mapping = aes(x = year,
                     y = behave,
                     col = genus)) +
  geom_line()

Code 
mean_weight <- mean_weight |>
  mutate(genus = as.factor(genus),
         genus = fct_reorder(genus, 
                               behave, 
                               .desc = TRUE))

ggplot(data = mean_weight,
       mapping = aes(x = year,
                     y = behave,
                     col = genus)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = 'timegrpah for mean weight and genus',
       y = '')

#3

Code 
week_levels <- c('Mon', 
                 'Tue',
                 'Wed',
                 'Thu',
                 'Fri',
                 'Sat',
                 'Sun')
rod_week <- surveys |>
  filter(!is.na(day_of_week)) |>
  group_by(day_of_week) |>
  summarise(Rodent_daily = n()) |>
  mutate(day_of_week = factor(day_of_week, levels = week_levels))

ggplot(data = rod_week,
       mapping = aes(x = day_of_week,
                     y = Rodent_daily)) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = day_of_week)) + 
  labs(y = '',
       x = 'Day of the Week',
       title = 'Rodent per Day')

Code 
rod_week$day_of_week <- fct_recode(rod_week$day_of_week, 
                                   weekday = "Mon",
                                   weekday = "Tue",
                                   weekday = "Wed",
                                   weekday = "Thu",
                                   weekday = "Fri",
                                   weekend = "Sat",
                                   weekend = "Sun")
day_or_end <- rod_week |>
  group_by(day_of_week) |>
  summarise(sum(Rodent_daily))

ggplot(data = day_or_end,
       mapping = aes(x = day_of_week,
                     y = `sum(Rodent_daily)`)) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = day_of_week)) + 
  labs(y = '',
       x = '',
       title = 'Rodents captured during the Week')

#1

```{r}
surveys <- surveys |>
  mutate(species = as.factor(species),
         species = fct_reorder(species, 
                               weight, 
                               .desc = TRUE))

ggplot(data = surveys, 
       mapping = aes (x = weight, 
                      y = species)) + 
  geom_jitter(color = 'tomato', 
              alpha = 0.2) + 
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA)  +
  labs(x = 'Weight(g)',
       y = '',
       title = 'Plot')
```


```{r}
mean_weight <- surveys |>
  group_by(year, 
           genus) |>
  summarise(behave = mean(weight))
ggplot(data = mean_weight,
       mapping = aes(x = year,
                     y = behave,
                     col = genus)) +
  geom_line()
```

```{r}
mean_weight <- mean_weight |>
  mutate(genus = as.factor(genus),
         genus = fct_reorder(genus, 
                               behave, 
                               .desc = TRUE))

ggplot(data = mean_weight,
       mapping = aes(x = year,
                     y = behave,
                     col = genus)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = 'timegrpah for mean weight and genus',
       y = '')
```

#3

```{r}
week_levels <- c('Mon', 
                 'Tue',
                 'Wed',
                 'Thu',
                 'Fri',
                 'Sat',
                 'Sun')
rod_week <- surveys |>
  filter(!is.na(day_of_week)) |>
  group_by(day_of_week) |>
  summarise(Rodent_daily = n()) |>
  mutate(day_of_week = factor(day_of_week, levels = week_levels))

ggplot(data = rod_week,
       mapping = aes(x = day_of_week,
                     y = Rodent_daily)) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = day_of_week)) + 
  labs(y = '',
       x = 'Day of the Week',
       title = 'Rodent per Day')

```

```{r}
rod_week$day_of_week <- fct_recode(rod_week$day_of_week, 
                                   weekday = "Mon",
                                   weekday = "Tue",
                                   weekday = "Wed",
                                   weekday = "Thu",
                                   weekday = "Fri",
                                   weekend = "Sat",
                                   weekend = "Sun")
day_or_end <- rod_week |>
  group_by(day_of_week) |>
  summarise(sum(Rodent_daily))

ggplot(data = day_or_end,
       mapping = aes(x = day_of_week,
                     y = `sum(Rodent_daily)`)) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = day_of_week)) + 
  labs(y = '',
       x = '',
       title = 'Rodents captured during the Week')
```
